\subsubsection*{Living Image (Inspire \textbullet)}

\noindent Requires: 2 dots in Crafts or Expression, and a speciality in a form of art

\noindent \textbf{Action:} Instant

\noindent \textbf{Dice Pool:} Inner Light + Presence 

\noindent \textbf{Cost:} 1 Wisp, 1 Willpower

\noindent \textbf{Duration:} Indefinite\\

\noindent Artists among the Hopeful have can infuse the Light into their art, and make it bring forth magic. This Charm enchants artwork, turning into a vessel to hold and invoke another Charm. The art to be enchanted may be created through mundane, technological or magical means but it must be a product of the Princess' creativity and it must be designed specifically to carry the chosen Charm. The art is about, means, the Charm it holds, so a wholly or partly finished work on another subject cannot carry the intended Charm.

The Princess first chooses the Charm, Upgrades, and  the precise effects (for example, which emotion the Charm Feel So Close will enhance) she desires. The Charm chosen must be one that affects a targeted individual, she cannot choose something like Levinbolt. Next the Princess creates art to express the ideas and emotions of the chosen charm, using the normal rules for creating equipment. The equipment bonus must equal the dots of the Charm the Princess wishes to cast, not counting any Upgrades. When the artwork is ready the Princess casts Living Image upon it to turn her art into a vessel. 


\begin{myindentpar}{10pt}\emph{Dramatic Failure:} The Noble’s magic goes out of control and ruins the artwork. She must recreate it from the beginning, using new materials
 
 \emph{Failure:} The Noble fails to prepare the artwork. Further attempts to use the Charm on it take a cumulative -1 penalty
 
 \emph{Success or Exceptional Success} The artwork becomes a valid target for the Charm it’s based on. The artwork becomes a container for her Charm and gains the Held Charm Condition: If the Princess casts the chosen Charm upon the artwork then she fills her container and that Charm will affect the next person who experiences the art in the proper way - a painting must be looked at, recorded music must be listened to etc. If the Princess invokes a Charm with Commonality then when the Charm is released it will affect the largest Commonality group among the present audience, within the limits of the dicepool penalty taken. The Condition is also renewable meaning that once the Charm is used up the Princess can simply invoke it upon the artwork again. Damage to the artwork ends the Condition (if the artwork must be damaged to be appreciated, such as culinary arts or fireworks, then the Charm takes effect 
before it is destroyed). 
 
\end{myindentpar}

The Princess may add Intimacy to her roll. If she does so only then the Charm within her artwork will only affect the targeted person, no matter how many people appreciate it before them. 

At any one time a Princess may have Inner Light + Belief different works of art enhanced with Living Image. Artwork that has used up it's Charm still counts towards this limit. If the Princess touches the art she can remove the enchantment without damaging the artwork to free up a slot. 

Gems created by the Specchio Charm Enduring Beauty can be used to empower art created by Living Image, doing so requires that the artwork revolves around a deception of the human form. As these are Brats, it's often a depiction of the Princess creating the artwork. 

The gems embedded in the artwork cause it to constantly produce Wisps allowing the art to replenish it's own Charm again and again. A gem worth Resources 3 produces 1 Wisp a day and always rolls two successes on it's internal Charm. A gem worth Resources 5 produces 2 Wisps a day and rolls three success. 

\begin{myindentpar}{10pt}\textbf{Upgrade: Composed}

The Princess does not enchant art, but instructions for creating art such as sheet music or a dance choreography. The instructions must be for a form of art where the instructions are followed in front of a live audience. 

Creating instructions follows the usual rules for this Charm. She creates the instructions first as mundane equipment then invokes Living Image upon them in order to apply the Held Charm Condition to her instructions. The Princess does not need to write anything down or otherwise create a physical object, she could apply Held Charm to performers directly, creating \textquotedblleft\, equipment\textquotedblright\, through a teaching session. However written instructions are easier to pass between different performers. 

From that point on, the Charm will activate upon someone who appreciates the artwork when the instructions are performed, as is usual for Living Image.    

\textbf{Upgrade: Duplicated}

While some methods of creating artwork do not lend themselves to duplication, others are the exact opposite. A story can be photocopied without loosing any of it's artistic value. 

With this upgrade a Princess can convert her artwork into vessels en mass. She could invoke Living Image on a computer document and start printing out copies or she could invoke Living Image on a bowl of cake mixture and start pouring it into individual cupcakes. Each instance of her artwork beyond the first costs one Wisp and all enchanted works must be created within the same scene. In addition each one must be filled with Charms independently, though at the Storyteller's discretion the player may be permitted to roll only once to keep the game moving quickly.

Duplicated artwork only counts as a single work towards the Princess' maximum uses of Living Image.

\textbf{Upgrade: Gallery}

Stacks, up to 4

The Princess can now sustain magic in more artwork. Each time she takes this upgrade, she adds two to the number of Living Image activations she may have up at once.

\textbf{Upgrade: Light Attuned}

The Princess may specify that her artwork will only invoke Charms upon Beacons, Princesses, Shikigami, Sworn, or any combination of those three groups. Alternatively, she may specify that her artwork won't affect the Light touched. 

\textbf{Upgrade: Remote}

The Princess may refill her artwork with fresh Charms without being in it's physical presence. She must modify her Charm activation roll by her Intimacy to the artwork itself. 

Remote can be combined with Duplicated, but not easily. Unless a Princess feels different emotions about the various copies of her artwork she will be unable to choose which copy she refills.

\textbf{Upgrade: Dark Attuned (Tempesta \textbullet)}

The Princess may specify that her artwork will only invoke Charms upon Creatures of the Darkness. She may not specify a specific kind of Dark Creature. 

And yes, with the right Charm it is indeed possible to create artwork that makes Darkspawn feel so bad they explode. After all, emotions are magic. 
\end{myindentpar}


