    \emph{Failure:} The Princess cannot quell the storm inisde. 

    \emph{Success:} So long as the target, who may be the Princess herself, remains within the designated area any mundane Conditions that affect her mind or emotion are suppressed. The Storyteller must use their own judgement for supernatural conditions. However a controlled environment is key. The Condition returns if the target is exposed to suitable stimulus, for example, if she opens the Facebook profile for the boy she's Swooned towards. If she leaves the designated area all the Conditions return and the Charm's effects upon her end. By carefully introducing the correct stimulus a Princess can reactivate and then Resolve her Conditions one at a time. Conditions that represent a short term emotional state (such as Spooked) can also be rendered harmless until they naturally expire but no Beats are awarded if the Condition is not Resolved. That said, a Princess who makes a habit of suppressing a long term mental health issue rather than resolving it will likely make the situation worse. 

    \emph{Exceptional Success:} So long as they remain in the affected area the target may voluntarily roll Resolve + Composure to prevent a stimulus from reactivating a Condition. 

\end{myindentpar}


