\subsubsection*{Second Glance Wrongness (Learn \textbullet\textbullet)}

\noindent Requires: Scent Falsehood

\noindent \textbf{Action:} Reflexive

\noindent \textbf{Cost:} none

\noindent \textbf{Dice Pool:} Clash of Wills

\noindent \textbf{Duration:} 1 turn \\

\noindent Sometimes magic gets you good. The Enlightened are all too aware of that. Sometimes your mind can be wrapped in irrational fear by the Dark-Spawn hanging from the ceiling, pale-faced, sometimes the warrior of Storms can drive you into a frenzy, some things can pass by invisible. Princesses learn, though, to listen to the subtle wrongness that they get when their senses are being messed with, and it's possible to stoke the radiance within, to burn away the clouds that fog the mind.

Whenever the Princess' mind is influenced or controlled by a supernatural power, the player may declare this Charm activates and make a Clash of Wills against whoever has influenced her mind.

This Charm may only be rolled once per scene. 

    \begin{myindentpar}{10pt}\emph{Dramatic Failure:} The Princess is so utterly fooled by the deceit that her mind is rendered susceptible to follow-up blows. She takes the Cursed condition, inflicting a -3 penalty to realise she is under a supernatural compulsion. This lasts for a day. 

    \emph{Failure:} Nothing happens.

    \emph{Success:} A distorted perception wavers for a moment, showing what it conceals; an imposed emotion falters, revealing the Princess’ true feelings; a compulsion falls slack, and is disclosed as instilled by another. The Princess may spend 1 Willpower point to bypass it for that action - penalties don’t apply, compulsions don’t restrict her

    \emph{Exceptional Success:}  The power holding the Princess’ mind slips. During the Princess’ next turn, she ignores its effects on her, without spending Willpower.\end{myindentpar}

\begin{myindentpar}{10pt}

\textbf{Upgrade: Meditative (Legno \textbullet\textbullet\textbullet)}

When the Princess sees through an illusion she may opt to enter a tranquil state instead of breaking free for a turn, the same Willpower cost applies. If the Princess chooses tranquillity she remains still, unmoving and unthinking, for Legno minutes. This is often enough for the Princess to fail at whatever crime she was forced to attempt. 

If the Princess is under an effect with a limited duration, the time she spends tranquil does count towards the duration.

\textbf{Upgrade: Furious (Tempesta \textbullet\textbullet\textbullet)}

A Fury can breaks free from enchantments through the pure cleansing power of hatred. If she succeeds on the roll and spends a Willpower point she remains free for as many turns as she spends attacking someone (guns, Charms, so long as she is trying her hardest to kill it doesn't matter how) or charging in the direction of someone she intends to attack. Furies have been known to go on frenzied rampages against anyone and everyone nearby to keep their minds free.

This is also notable for being one of the more common results of a Royal Favour from the Queen of Storms. 

\textbf{Upgrade: Unbroken (Lacrima \textbullet\textbullet\textbullet\textbullet)}

Alhambra has stood unbroken in the face of the Darkness' hunger, and her Nobility can remain unbroken in the heart of their enemies enchantments. On a Success the Princess may opt break free for up to Lacrima + Inner Light turns at the cost of one Willpower. \end{myindentpar}

